# qodana-dotnet — Qodana Ultimate for .NET/Rider (image name = repoName). Feed code QDNET. Internal
# nightly dist feed: unsigned tar.gz, sha256-only (no GPG .asc), eap (the nightly feed is eap-only); the build
# mounts QODANA_READ_SPACE_PACKAGES_TOKEN (compose.private.yaml).
# Distinct from the Community qodana-cdnet (which ships the ReSharper CLT tool binary, no IDE dist).
#
# Builds on the SHARED trixie debian-base (the same QD_TRIXIE_BASE_IMAGE as jvm-community/python(-community)/
# rust), which ships NO .NET, so it layers the SHARED dotnet-toolchain install stage (.NET SDK 8/9/10 via the
# pinned dotnet-install.sh) — the same lib/toolchain/dotnet.dockerfile cdnet uses. Rider analyzes JS/TS (the
# upstream Rider base layers node + a global eslint), so — like go/php/ruby — dotnet also LAYERS the node
# toolchain (NODE_MAJOR) + the in-place eslint pin. NuGet/dotnet caches live in the writable $HOME
# (lib/base --create-home's the qodana user) — NO /data/cache redirect (and /data/cache is bind-mounted
# EMPTY at scan time anyway).
#
# Rider scans shell out to sudo (source PRIVILEGED=true), so dotnet INCLUDEs lib/privileged.dockerfile and its
# dist FROMs the privileged stage. dotnet is the FIRST dist+privileged+dotnet-toolchain image:
#   DIST_BASE_STAGE=privileged is an .env KEY (base.dockerfile does NOT default DIST_BASE_STAGE, so the
#     INCLUDE_ARGS value survives to `FROM ${DIST_BASE_STAGE:-base} AS dist` — the android/php/ruby convention).
#   PRIVILEGED_BASE_STAGE=dotnet-toolchain is its dual — a COMPOSE BUILD ARG only (base.dockerfile defaults it
#     to clang-toolchain, which would clobber an .env value, so --build-arg must win — the cdnet convention),
#     so it is NOT here. So privileged FROMs dotnet-toolchain, dist FROMs privileged.
# LIBICU_PKG=libicu76: the shared dotnet toolchain apt-installs ${LIBICU_PKG:-libicu72}; the trixie base needs
#   libicu76 (cdnet's bookworm default libicu72 stays via the use-site fallback — cdnet's .env is unchanged).
# uid 1000 is FREE on the trixie base, so default 1000, NO uid keys (the source uses 1001; lib/base creates the
# qodana user at the free 1000 — the rust/ruby divergence, phase-0). eslint is pinned in
# lib/toolchain/eslint/package.json (renovate). Pins live in docs/phase-0-decisions.md; DotnetEnvContractTest
# asserts byte-identity for the dist pins + the trixie base digest. Key set = ruby's key set + LIBICU_PKG.
QD_LINTER_SLUG=qodana-dotnet
QD_VERSION=2026.3
# renovate: datasource=custom.qodana-dist depName=qodana-dotnet versioning=loose
QD_BUILD=263.136.1738
QD_DISTRIBUTION_FEED=https://packages.jetbrains.team/files/p/sa/qodana-dist-internal/feed
QD_VERIFY_MODE=sha256
QD_PRODUCT_INFO_CODE=RD
QD_BASE_IMAGE=dhi.io/debian-base:trixie-debian13-dev@sha256:68b5f4c2c789b99dc6ab7574c7e695e724646f64616619c48c3245f8aaeae459
DIST_BASE_STAGE=privileged
LIBICU_PKG=libicu76
CLI_BINARY=qodana
CLI_VERSION=2026.2
CLI_OS=linux
NODE_MAJOR=20
